  %body
    .container
      .row
        .box
          .col-lg-12
            %hr
              %h2.intro-text.text-center
                FAQ
              %hr
                %ol
                  %li
                    %a{:href => resources_path + '#meetingTimes'}When does the club meet?
                  %li
                    %a{:href => resources_path + '#events'}Where can I find a list of club events?
                  %li
                    %a{:href => resources_path + '#languageChoice'}What language(s) should I learn?
                  %li
                    %a{:href => resources_path + '#hobbyist'}Can I learn to program as a hobby?
                  %li
                    %a{:href => resources_path + '#interviewPrep'}How should I prepare for a technical interview?
                  %li
                    %a{:href => resources_path + '#careers'}What kind of careers are there in computer science?
                  %li
                    %a{:href => resources_path + '#clubReqs'}I don't want to be a computer science major. Can I join the club?
                  %li
                    %a{:href => resources_path + '#challenges'}Where can I go to improve my programming skills?
      .row
        .box
          .col-lg-12
            %hr
              %h2.intro-text.text-center
                Answers
              %hr
                %p Don't like our answers, or are we missing a question? Email us suggestions here! (NYI link to email us)
                %ol
                  %li
                    %a{:name => 'meetingTimes'}
                    The Mills Computer Club meets Thursdays at 4 PM in Stern 14. On weeks where there are guest speakers or workshops, we instead meet at the advertised location.
                    %br
                    There are many other events throughout the week or month. For more details, please visit
                    %a{:href => events_path}our calendar!
                  %li
                    %a{:name => 'events'}
                    Our events are listed on
                    %a{:href => events_path}our calendar,
                    where you are encouraged to RSVP. If you have any questions about the event, or would like to suggest a presentation, please
                    %a{:href => root_path + '#contactUs'}contact us!
                  %li
                    %a{:name => 'languageChoice'}
                    Here are the resources endorsed by the Mills Computer Club members:
                    %br
                    Python ->
                    %a{:href => 'http://learnpythonthehardway.org/book/'}Learn Python the Hard Way
                    %br
                    Ruby ->
                    %a{:href => 'http://www.codecademy.com/en/tracks/ruby'}Codecademy
                    %br
                    More coming soon.
                  %li
                    %a{:name => 'hobbyist'}
                    You can learn on your own.
                  %li
                    %a{:name => 'interviewPrep'}
                    Interview preparation.
                  %li
                    %a{:name => 'careers'}
                    Careers.
                  %li
                    %a{:name => 'clubReqs'}
                    Of course! Our club members are mostly computer science students, but we welcome everyone -- academics and hobbyists alike. The club is perfect for interdisciplinary interests, such as business students wishing to manage technical teams, artists looking to do graphic design, and writers wanting a career in technical writing.
                  %li
                    %a{:name => 'challenges'}
                    HackerRank, Project Euler, TopCoder, codingbat.

    / /.container

    / jQuery
    %script{:src => "js/jquery.js"}
    / Bootstrap Core JavaScript
    %script{:src => "js/bootstrap.min.js"}
